<subSubSection id="C351E8E4FFF9FFB3FF5B352BFB28F92F" pageId="3" pageNumber="495" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF4BB6FFFF9FFB3FF5B352BFE20FA6C" blockId="3.[151,1436,1361,1748]" pageId="3" pageNumber="495">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF9FFB3FF5B352BFEBDFA97" bold="true" box="[199,317,1361,1387]" pageId="3" pageNumber="495">Remarks:</emphasis>
In the present observation one ciliate specimen was found as epibiont attached to the middle part of the host 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BC0ECFFF9FFB3FF6A350FFE20FA6C" box="[246,416,1397,1424]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Desmodora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="495" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF9FFB3FF6A350FFEF9FA73" box="[246,377,1397,1423]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="495">Desmodora</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF4BB6FFFF9FFB3FF0B35E3FADFF99B" blockId="3.[151,1436,1361,1748]" pageId="3" pageNumber="495">
This species was reported earlier as epibiont on nematodes 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BC0ECFFF9FFB3FCDE35E3FB7AFA4F" authority="Claparede, 1863" authorityName="Claparede" authorityYear="1863" box="[834,1274,1433,1459]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmoscolecidae" genus="Desmoscolex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmoscolecida" pageId="3" pageNumber="495" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF9FFB3FCDE35E3FBB8FA4F" box="[834,1080,1433,1459]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="495">Desmoscolex minutus</emphasis>
Claparède, 1863
</taxonomicName>
from Istanbul Strait’s area in Bosporus region of the Black Sea at 
<quantity id="4CB3168AFFF9FFB3FD7A35C7FCC4FA24" box="[742,836,1469,1496]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.524" pageId="3" pageNumber="495" unit="m" value="252.4">252.4 m</quantity>
depth (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAC69EFFF9FFB3FC0635C7FB47FA24" author="Sergeeva, N. G. &amp; Dovgal, I." box="[922,1223,1469,1496]" pageId="3" pageNumber="495" pagination="596 - 600" refId="ref4162" refString="Sergeeva, N. G. &amp; Dovgal, I. (2016) Loricophrya bosporica n. sp. (Ciliophora, Suctorea) epibiont of Desmoscolex cf. minutus (Nematoda, Desmoscolecida) from oxic / anoxic boundary of the Black Sea Istanbul Strait's outlet area. Zootaxa, 4061 (5), 596 - 600. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4061.5.9" type="journal article" year="2016">Sergeeva &amp; Dovgal, 2016</bibRefCitation>
). This was also reported as epibiont on 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BC0ECFFF9FFB3FE1B359BFC0DFA00" authority="(Gerlach, 1951)" baseAuthorityName="Gerlach" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[391,909,1505,1532]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Metachromadoroides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="495" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="remanei">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF9FFB3FE1B359BFD57FA07" box="[391,727,1505,1531]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="495">Metachromadoroides remanei</emphasis>
