</taxonomicName>
from methane seep of the Ria 
<collectingCountry id="F35CFBFFFFF9FFB3FB7D3598FAC3FA00" box="[1249,1347,1506,1532]" name="Taiwan" pageId="3" pageNumber="495">Formosa</collectingCountry>
lagoon, Southern 
<collectingCountry id="F35CFBFFFFF9FFB3FE99367FFEE4F9E3" box="[261,356,1541,1567]" name="Portugal" pageId="3" pageNumber="495">Portugal</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAC69EFFF9FFB3FEE8367FFDD7F9E3" author="Ivanova, E. &amp; Dovgal, I. V. &amp; Newton, A." box="[372,599,1541,1568]" pageId="3" pageNumber="495" pagination="51 - 57" refId="ref3656" refString="Ivanova, E., Dovgal, I. V. &amp; Newton, A. (2017) First records of epibiont ciliates (Ciliophora) in methane enriched sediments with species redescriptions. Ecologica Montenegrina, 10, 51 - 57. https: // doi. org / 10.37828 / em. 2017.10.8" type="journal article" year="2017">
Ivanova 
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF9FFB3FE44367CFD8BF9E3" box="[472,523,1541,1567]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="495">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAC69EFFF9FFB3FDF7367FFCEAF9E3" author="Baldrighi, E. &amp; Dovgal, I. &amp; Zeppilli, D. &amp; Abibulaeva, A. &amp; Michelet, C. &amp; Michaud, E. &amp; Franzo, A. &amp; Grassi, E. &amp; Cesaroni, L. &amp; Guidi, L. &amp; Balsamo, M. &amp; Sandulli, R. &amp; Semprucci, F." box="[619,874,1541,1568]" pageId="3" pageNumber="495" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref3187" refString="Baldrighi, E., Dovgal, I., Zeppilli, D., Abibulaeva, A., Michelet, C., Michaud, E., Franzo, A., Grassi, E., Cesaroni, L., Guidi, L., Balsamo, M., Sandulli, R. &amp; Semprucci, F. (2020) The cost for biodiversity: records of ciliate - nematode epibiosis with the description of three new suctorian species. Diversity, 12 (6), Article No. 224, 1 - 25. https: // doi. org / 10.3390 / d 12060224" type="book chapter" year="2020">
Baldrighi 
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF9FFB3FD41367CFC90F9E3" box="[733,784,1541,1567]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="495">et al</emphasis>
. (2020)
</bibRefCitation>
reported the species as epibiont on nematodes of genera 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BC0ECFFF9FFB3FF743653FEEBF9BF" box="[232,363,1577,1603]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Desmodora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="495" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF9FFB3FF743653FEEBF9BF" box="[232,363,1577,1603]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="495">Desmodora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BC0ECFFF9FFB3FE3C3653FD70F9BF" authority="Claparede, 1863" authorityName="Claparede" authorityYear="1863" box="[416,752,1577,1603]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmoscolecidae" genus="Desmoscolex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmoscolecida" pageId="3" pageNumber="495" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF9FFB3FE3C3653FDB4F9BF" box="[416,564,1577,1603]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="495">Desmoscolex</emphasis>
Claparède, 1863
</taxonomicName>
from Gulf of Naples (Mediterranean, Tyrrhenian Sea)—shallow vent area and 
<collectingCountry id="F35CFBFFFFF9FFB3FEF83637FD8AF99B" box="[356,522,1613,1639]" name="French Guiana" pageId="3" pageNumber="495">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
(South America, Atlantic Ocean)—Mangrove forest (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAC69EFFF9FFB3FBF83637FAD3F99B" author="Baldrighi, E. &amp; Dovgal, I. &amp; Zeppilli, D. &amp; Abibulaeva, A. &amp; Michelet, C. &amp; Michaud, E. &amp; Franzo, A. &amp; Grassi, E. &amp; Cesaroni, L. &amp; Guidi, L. &amp; Balsamo, M. &amp; Sandulli, R. &amp; Semprucci, F." box="[1124,1363,1613,1640]" pageId="3" pageNumber="495" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref3187" refString="Baldrighi, E., Dovgal, I., Zeppilli, D., Abibulaeva, A., Michelet, C., Michaud, E., Franzo, A., Grassi, E., Cesaroni, L., Guidi, L., Balsamo, M., Sandulli, R. &amp; Semprucci, F. (2020) The cost for biodiversity: records of ciliate - nematode epibiosis with the description of three new suctorian species. Diversity, 12 (6), Article No. 224, 1 - 25. https: // doi. org / 10.3390 / d 12060224" type="book chapter" year="2020">
Baldrighi 
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF9FFB3FB4B3634FA88F99B" box="[1239,1288,1613,1639]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="495">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF4BB6FFFF9FFB3FF5B360BFF60F94C" blockId="3.[151,1436,1361,1748]" pageId="3" pageNumber="495">
The species was found on nematode hosts only and was mentioned as extremophile (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAC69EFFF9FFB3FB29360BFF54F94C" author="Sergeeva, N. G. &amp; Dovgal, I." pageId="3" pageNumber="495" pagination="596 - 600" refId="ref4162" refString="Sergeeva, N. G. &amp; Dovgal, I. (2016) Loricophrya bosporica n. sp. (Ciliophora, Suctorea) epibiont of Desmoscolex cf. minutus (Nematoda, Desmoscolecida) from oxic / anoxic boundary of the Black Sea Istanbul Strait's outlet area. Zootaxa, 4061 (5), 596 - 600. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4061.5.9" type="journal article" year="2016">Dovgal &amp; Sergeeva 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF4BB6FFFF9FFB3FF0B36C3FB28F92F" blockId="3.[151,1436,1361,1748]" box="[151,1192,1721,1748]" pageId="3" pageNumber="495">The present find is the first report of this species from the Arabian Sea and the Indian Ocean.</paragraph>
